{
  "texts": [
    "As the missing data is filled, additional information is introduced, leading to higher correlation coefficients between company sentiment features.",
    "The second heat map also shows clearer patterns or clusters of correlation, indicating that the Transformer model may have grouped certain companies based on sentiment similarity.",
    "Forecast TransformerThe Forecast Transformer (FT) (Figure 5) uses an encoder-decoder architecture for stock price prediction and the detailed illustration of the input dimension is shown in Figure 6.",
    "The encoder processes a 5-day sliding window of historical market data that contains three key elements: (1) daily close prices, (2) sentiment features, and (3) time features (day of week, month, and day of month).",
    "These inputs are combined through a special embedding layer, where each component is processed separately [32]."
  ]
}